      "content": "i get that but i'm just looking for some general info. i've read online that if your blood work is stable you can actually taper down to a lower maintenance dose. like, if my levels are good, isn't it actually safer to be on a smaller dose so i don't overdo it? wouldnt 2mg be a reasonable amount for someone who's feeling healthy and has stable levels?",
